         <abstract>
            <p>It is proved, with the help of a computer, that for m = 20 the first m minimal elements for the sequence of all powers in an integer-representing algorithm are given by y&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; = i, i = 1, 2, 3, y&lt;sub&gt;i + 1&lt;/sub&gt; = (y&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; + 6y&lt;sub&gt;i&lt;/sub&gt; + 1)/4, i = 3, ..., m - 1. This extends an earlier result of the author (for m = 10).</p>
          </abstract>
